It's hot. Be careful.

28
00:04:37,030 --> 00:04:41,970
What is this? What kind of house has such a bad heating system?

29
00:04:41,970 --> 00:04:44,380
It's just uselessly huge.

30
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:49,020
Isn't it true that you actually like Yo Han too?

31
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:50,510
- What? 
 - If you think about it..

32
00:04:50,510 --> 00:04:56,160
You helped find the prison in America and I think you did it because you thought it was meaningful.

33
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:58,980
- It's fun. 
 - Fun?

34
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:03,080
Maybe it would've been more fun they cut it off.

35
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:08,100
No wonder you're all family.

36
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:10,100
Don't say that.

37
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:14,660
Yo Han destroys everything near him.

38
00:05:15,970 --> 00:05:18,270
I hate people like that.

39
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:19,910
What do you mean?

40
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:22,990
You didn't hear from the ajumma?

41
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:25,560
They said Yo Han was like that ever since he was young.

42
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:30,440
He made the housemaid who liked him jump from the second floor.

43
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:34,060
Even Dad...

44
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:37,920
and even me...

45
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:01,740
You still have that habit.

46
00:06:01,740 --> 00:06:04,790
Not knowing your place and the habit of touching everything.

47
00:06:04,790 --> 00:06:10,090
Oh, Young Master, you recognize me only now?

48
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:21,770
 My goodness, how are they so pretty? 

49
00:06:21,770 --> 00:06:25,600
  I didn't even know a world like this existed. 

50
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,790
  A world full of only pretty things! 

51
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:30,860
  Don't make a fuss and focus on learning your job. 

52
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:34,030
  What do you have to do in order to live like this? 

53
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:36,590
  Do I have to be born again? 
 - Tsk tsk. 

54
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:39,780
  The chairman doesn't like talkative people. 

55
00:06:39,780 --> 00:06:42,380
 If you don't want to be kicked out, close your mouth. 

56
00:06:42,380 --> 00:06:47,990
  What about Master Yo Han? How could he be so pretty and handsome? 

57
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:50,190
  How could they put someone like that in the basement? 

58
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:51,960
  Stop! 

59
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:04,980
  Please eat, Young Master. I prepared it for you. 

60
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:09,040
  Thanks. 

61
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:16,390
  When the chairman isn't home, you should go outside. I'll be the lookout for you. 

62
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,940
  Do you like me? 

63
00:07:59,940 --> 00:08:02,060
  Yes. 

64
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:04,350
  How much do you like me? 

65
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:06,330
  Huh? 

66
00:08:06,330 --> 00:08:08,420
  I said, how much do you like me? 

67
00:08:09,370 --> 00:08:12,130
  A lot. Very very much. 

68
00:08:12,130 --> 00:08:14,000
  Really? 

69
00:08:15,850 --> 00:08:18,420
  Then, can you jump from here? 

70
00:08:18,420 --> 00:08:20,200
  What? 

71
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:23,160
  Can you do that for me?  

72
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,950
  Really? 

73
00:08:40,950 --> 00:08:42,920
  Seon Ah! 

74
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:03,600
You were so mean.

75
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,900
I liked you so much.

76
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:12,060
Ridiculous. I'm sure what you liked was something else.

77
00:09:22,990 --> 00:09:25,430
  If I were you, I wouldn't do that. 

78
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:28,110
 Young Master! 

79
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:33,390
  If you get caught, it won't end well. That person doesn't know forgiveness. 

80
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:37,710
  Are you worrying about me now? 

81
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:42,330
  You're worried about me, right? 

82
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:48,720
  I like you so much, Young Master. Don't you like me? 

83
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:59,620
  That's weird ... it seems that things have been going missing lately. 

84
00:09:59,620 --> 00:10:01,520
  Really? 

85
00:10:02,610 --> 00:10:07,350
  Truthfully, there has been something on my mind recently too... 

86
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:08,980
  What is it? 

87
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:13,780
  I am cautious in saying this but.. 

88
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:17,200
 Young Master Yo Han has been going outside often recently 

89
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,900
  Even though the Chairman told him to stay in the basement. 

90
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:25,560
  - Is that so? 
 - Yes, I'm worried. 

91
00:10:50,530 --> 00:10:52,830
  Not that! 

92
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:57,400
  That's my older brother's memento left by his mother. He cherishes that! 

93
00:10:57,400 --> 00:11:01,170
  If you touch that, I'll report everything I saw. 

94
00:11:01,170 --> 00:11:03,940
  I was just looking at it because it was so pretty! 

95
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:08,420
  If I laid a hand on Madam's stuff, I would die in the Chairman's hands! 

96
00:11:59,540 --> 00:12:01,950
  Do you like me? 

97
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:07,150
  Then, can you jump off from here? 

98
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:29,740
Oh? Did I?

99
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:34,140
You have such good memory, Young Master. You're really smart.

100
00:12:36,810 --> 00:12:39,130
But still, I did like you.

101
00:12:39,130 --> 00:12:44,490
I've always liked everything that sparkles, you see.

102
00:12:44,490 --> 00:12:47,490
Whether then, or now.

103
00:12:47,490 --> 00:12:50,660
Really? It seems that you worked hard all your life.

104
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:54,680
So are you playing the maid

105
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:57,300
while stealing things here and there at the foundation, now?

106
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:23,440
You are impressive, Young Master.

107
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:27,920
You eliminated your idiotic older brother and then played the hero,

108
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:31,830
coming out of there holding his daughter in your arms so you wouldn't be suspected.

109
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:38,000
I can't help but to fall for you.

110
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:45,950
What makes you think Yo Han did it? There must have been something that convinced you.

111
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:49,350
- His computer. 
 - His computer?

112
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:55,120
When I was twelve, I unlocked Yo Han's computer for fun.

113
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:59,710
There was a hidden folder, so I looked through it.

114
00:13:59,710 --> 00:14:03,790
And it was in there.

115
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:06,820
The form to cancel the donation pledge.

116
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:10,270
Also, the date it was created was

117
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:14,180
a week before the fire erupted.

118
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:22,710
To me, Yo Han was all I had.

119
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:25,220
To me...

120
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:51,700
Stop talking about past events and get to the point.

121
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:55,430
Shall I?

122
00:14:56,110 --> 00:15:01,260
I don't care whether you play trial in court or steam and eat Cha Gyeong Hui.

123
00:15:01,260 --> 00:15:04,320
But I'd like it if you laid off your interest on our foundation.

124
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:10,150
Young Master, you're trying to interfere now with the ranches of sheep that have been carefully nurtured by others.

125
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:16,000
That Dream Village or whatever you're doing must be a very sparkling project.

126
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:18,390
You know you and I are in the same type.

127
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:21,790
If we don't invade each other's territory, a lot of interesting things could hap—

128
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:25,890
If I were you, I wouldn't do this. It's a waste of time.

129
00:15:25,890 --> 00:15:29,780
Right now, it would be better if you killed me, when you have the chance.

130
00:15:29,780 --> 00:15:31,600
That's faster.

131
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:37,100
Because never again ... will you be able to capture me like this.

132
00:15:38,490 --> 00:15:42,140
- If this is how you act— 
 - Your threats are meaningless.

133
00:15:42,140 --> 00:15:47,740
For me, there is nothing... to protect.

134
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:49,600
Really?

135
00:16:01,930 --> 00:16:04,310
Such a waste.

136
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:26,580
You stabbed him yourself, but what's with that reaction?

137
00:16:26,580 --> 00:16:30,360
The thing I'm afraid of most in this world is needles.

138
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:33,290
Ah, sure, sure.

139
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:39,780
Jae Hui? Take our Young Master back to his house.

140
00:16:39,780 --> 00:16:43,590
Huh? Why don't you finish him off, as he said himself?

141
00:16:43,590 --> 00:16:47,900
No, a sheep dog needs a wolf.

142
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:53,530
The more disruptive Kang Yo Han is, the more the Foundation leaders have no choice but to rely on me.

143
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:58,400
Still, this friend is too fearless.

144
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:08,760
Nothing to protect?

145
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:22,320
There is no such human being.

146
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:37,150
Chief, where did you go yesterday?

147
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:41,360
You're even interested in my personal life now?

148
00:19:42,060 --> 00:19:44,790
I was with a tough woman, should I tell you about it?

149
00:19:44,790 --> 00:19:47,140
She pulled my hair and kissed—

150
00:19:47,140 --> 00:19:49,710
Ah, that's enough.

151
00:20:12,390 --> 00:20:14,200
Ga On.

152
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,890
Yeah?

153
00:20:15,890 --> 00:20:19,070
- Open that for me. 
 - Huh?

154
00:20:19,070 --> 00:20:21,690
I said, open that for me.

155
00:20:23,620 --> 00:20:25,630
Yes, yes.

156
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:29,920
- Here? 
 - Yeah.

157
00:20:32,220 --> 00:20:34,770
You're going to eat ramen this early in the morning?

158
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:37,160
Pour water and bring it to me.

159
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:11,970
Elijah.

160
00:21:12,830 --> 00:21:14,900
What about my ramen?

161
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:17,130
Let's eat rice, not ramen.

162
00:21:17,130 --> 00:21:18,550
Rice?

163
00:21:19,390 --> 00:21:21,210
Chief, come and eat.

164
00:21:21,210 --> 00:21:24,100
Why suddenly rice?

165
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:27,690
I'm tired of this family. Let's eat rice like normal human beings.

166
00:21:27,690 --> 00:21:30,320
I'm living off this house so I made some food. So hurry and come..

167
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:32,730
Chief, you hurry and come too.

168
00:21:39,940 --> 00:21:43,390
What? Who said I wanted him to make food? Such a busybody.

169
00:21:43,390 --> 00:21:46,360
The corner of your mouth is smiling.

170
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:48,250
What are you saying?

171
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:54,290
What is that unpleasant expression?

172
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:55,860
I'm just amazed.

173
00:21:55,860 --> 00:21:58,730
Why are you amazed?

174
00:21:58,730 --> 00:22:03,320
Why are you looking at Kim Ga On's butt with such yearning?

175
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:05,860
- When did I ever— 
 - Hurry and come!

176
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:07,520
- Ah, okay! 
 - Ah, okay!

177
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:09,990
I'm going to kill you!

178
00:22:22,380 --> 00:22:24,030
Is this supposed to be "simple"?

179
00:22:24,030 --> 00:22:27,070
 Should I order some more salmon, Master Ga On?  

180
00:22:27,070 --> 00:22:28,990
Yes, and some celery too.

181
00:22:28,990 --> 00:22:30,890
"Master Ga On"?

182
00:22:30,890 --> 00:22:33,100
But this is Korean food.

183
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:35,120
You don't like Korean food?

184
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:37,640
I think I was a food-testing palace maid in my past life. 
   (palace maid who tested the king's food) 

185
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:41,130
I hate Korean food so much. I must have died from poison while food-testing.

186
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:44,270
All right, don't eat it if you don't want to.

187
00:22:44,270 --> 00:22:46,750
I'll taste it to see how bad it is.

188
00:22:46,750 --> 00:22:49,280
There will be no poison.

189
00:23:00,330 --> 00:23:02,070
What are you doing? Eat.

190
00:23:03,020 --> 00:23:05,940
I said this before, but I don't know taste.

191
00:23:05,940 --> 00:23:09,410
I just chew and swallow.

192
00:23:19,230 --> 00:23:22,300
You must really not have any taste.

193
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:31,070
But ... why are you doing this all of a sudden?

194
00:23:31,070 --> 00:23:34,690
I told you. I should at least make some food since I'm living off you people.

195
00:23:34,690 --> 00:23:38,690
I'm telling you beforehand, but I decline any sympathy.

196
00:23:38,690 --> 00:23:41,280
I'm not in the position of such luxury.

197
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:43,470
Do you want fruit? Tell me if you need anything else.

198
00:23:43,470 --> 00:23:44,870
All right.

199
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:49,940
Where did you learn how to cook?

200
00:23:50,620 --> 00:23:52,530
- What do you mean "learn"? 
 - Then what?

201
00:23:52,530 --> 00:23:56,090
Sixteen years as the son of restaurant owners and living alone for thirteen years.

202
00:23:56,090 --> 00:23:59,730
If you're the son of restaurant owners, aren't you still the son of restaurant owners?

203
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:02,280
Did your parents stop running their restaurant?

204
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,920
It just ended up like that.

205
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,330
Have some kiwi.

206
00:24:11,330 --> 00:24:14,220
W-what is this?

207
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,440
Young Master.

208
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:24,040
This unfamiliar harmony that doesn't fit with this house ... what is this?

209
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:25,620
Young Master.

210
00:24:27,220 --> 00:24:29,640
You don't even lay a finger on the food that I make.

211
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:33,000
Ajumoni, I saved some for you too.

212
00:24:40,260 --> 00:24:41,780
Elijah.

213
00:24:44,030 --> 00:24:48,000
- You're not sleeping yet, right? 
 - I'm still digesting.

214
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:52,620
It didn't taste too bad, but I'm not the type who can eat too much.

215
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:55,500
Oh, really? That was a week's worth.

216
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:57,150
Stop exaggerating.

217
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:01,230
- Do you have time tomorrow? 
 - Huh?

218
00:25:02,410 --> 00:25:08,780
I don't know... I might have to check. But why?

219
00:25:08,780 --> 00:25:12,550
If it's all right with you, I want to take you to meet someone.

220
00:25:12,550 --> 00:25:16,460
Meet with someone?

221
00:25:17,670 --> 00:25:19,560
But who?

222
00:25:20,580 --> 00:25:23,420
- My friend. 
 - Friend?

223
00:25:32,580 --> 00:25:36,520
- Hello. 
 - You're here? Sit inside.

224
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:41,380
Hello, Miss Elijah.

225
00:25:43,470 --> 00:25:46,700
I'm just Yun Su Hyeon.

226
00:25:46,700 --> 00:25:51,260
I heard a lot from Ga On. This guy usually isn't the type to worry about anyone else.

227
00:25:51,260 --> 00:25:55,080
- Don't distort the facts. 
 - What is your relationship?

228
00:25:57,280 --> 00:26:01,150
- Why? 
 - We're friends. Did Ga On not tell you?

229
00:26:01,150 --> 00:26:04,500
He didn't say that his friend was this pretty.

230
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:07,160
- She's pretty? 
 - Why are you laughing?

231
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:10,960
You're way prettier than me, Miss Elijah.

232
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:12,630
That's true.

233
00:26:14,030 --> 00:26:18,110
I'm sorry I overdid, but I figured it'd be nice if you had a sister-like figure close to you.

234
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:24,210
Next time, would it be all right if we talked casually? Or you can call me "eonni."

235
00:26:24,210 --> 00:26:26,440
That sounds good.

236
00:26:27,730 --> 00:26:33,150
I don't want to. I'm not a little kid anymore. In four years, I'll be twenty.

237
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,590
That's right.

238
00:26:36,590 --> 00:26:39,760
All right, Miss Elijah.

239
00:27:11,090 --> 00:27:14,720
- Where's Elijah? 
 - I haven't seen her either.

240
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:25,980
The file that you said you found on the computer, do you have it?

241
00:27:31,290 --> 00:27:34,310
- No. 
 - Su Hyeon, why did you ask that?

242
00:27:34,310 --> 00:27:36,410
I was just wondering.

243
00:27:38,070 --> 00:27:43,090
Elijah, donating a whole fortune is immoderate.

244
00:27:43,090 --> 00:27:47,680
He might've cancelled it for you or there could've been some inaccuracy in the date while creating the computer file.

245
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:51,030
No, I want us to confirm things.

246
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:02,300
Chief, how—

247
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:05,410
Do you not know what abduction of a minor is?

248
00:28:05,410 --> 00:28:08,000
Please stop this, Judge.

249
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:13,020
If you do anything to this child, I won't let it slide. Whoever that may be.

250
00:28:20,770 --> 00:28:22,520
I'm all right.

251
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,670
- I won't get in. 
 - Don't act childishly.

252
